{"title_page": "Nikki Valdez", "text_new": "{{short description|Filipino actress}}\n{{BLP sources|date=January 2013}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name         = Nikki Valdez\n| image        = \n| birth_name   = Ma. Alinica Valdez Garcia\n| birth_date   = {{birth date and age|1979|1|25}}\n| birth_place  = [[San Pedro, Laguna]]    [[Philippines]]\n| occupation   = [[Actress]], [[TV personality]]\n| years_active = 1993\u2013present\n| agent        = [[Star Magic]] (1993\u2013present)<br />[[ABS-CBN Entertainment]]<br />(1993\u2013present)\n| homepage     = \n| notable role = \n}}\n'''Ma. Alinica Valdez Garcia''', also known by her screen name '''Nikki Valdez''' (born January 25, 1979), is a [[Filipino people|Filipino]] actress and singer.\n\nShe is best known to play supporting roles to lead actors such as [[Jolina Magdangal]] (''Hey Babe'') in 1999 and [[Claudine Barretto]] (''Got 2 Believe'') in 2002. In 2003, she played the role of an older sister in ''[[Ang Tanging Ina]]''. She would later star in the late [[Wenn V. Deramas|Wenn Deramas]]' later works. In 2007, she came back to TV in the soap opera ''Walang Kapalit'' with Claudine Barretto and [[Piolo Pascual]] as the leads.\n\n==Career==\nIn the music scene she was known for a ballad called \"Meron Ba?\", for the soundtrack of ''G-Mik the Movie'' and ''Trip the Movie'' (2002), and starred in the lead role for ''F.L.A.M.E.S'' (1996-2002) TV series. She resumed her career soon after marrying a Canadian and having a baby. Valdez making her comeback to daytime television in the second installment of ''[[Precious Hearts Romances Presents|Precious Hearts Romances]]'' offering with ''Ang Lalaking Nagmahal sa Akin'' after her last role in ''[[Walang Kapalit]]'' in 2007. She worked with [[Kaye Abad]] and fellow newcomer Guji Lorenzana in Precious Hearts Romances third installment ''Somewhere in My Heart'' as Amanda in 2009.\n\nIn 2010, she is working on a daytime soap opera loosely based on the film ''[[Magkano ang Iyong Dangal?]]'' and co-starred with [[John Lloyd Cruz]] and [[Angel Locsin]] in the second book and second season of the successful TV series ''[[Imortal]]''.\n\nIn 2012, she worked along with Star Magic Alumni and Kapamilya Actress [[Shaina Magdayao]] and [[Jake Cuenca]] and along again with ''Magkano Ang Iyong Dangal?'' co-star [[Bangs Garcia]] in the top rated afternoon soap ''[[Kung Ako'y Iiwan Mo]]''.\n\n==Filmography==\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" <!-- Do not center -->\n|- <!-- Never add unnecessary background colors -->\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes <!-- Do not replace with or add a Network/Channel column. Network rivalry is outside of Wikipedia. Do not replace with an Episode column, Notes column is not limited to episode titles. -->\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Source <!-- Use third party sources other than the actor's IMDB page -->\n|- <!-- Do not add rowspan -->\n| 1993-02 \n| ''[[Home Along Da Riles]]'' \n| Becky Kosme\n|\n|\n|-\n| 1997\u2013present\n| ''[[ASAP (variety show)|ASAP]]'' \n| Co-host/Performer\n|\n|\n|-\n| 1999 \n| ''[[Gimik]]'' \n| Jek-jek\n|\n|\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''[[Kasaysayan TV]]''\n| Herself\n| As VJ-AP\n| <ref>{{Cite AV media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=o0Bg3NlaOEU|title=Ep 2: Ang Batayang Heograpikal ng Pilipinas (Part 1)(KTV)|publisher=[[YouTube]]|date=October 27, 2010|accessdate=23 January 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2003 \n| ''[[Ok Fine 'To Ang Gusto Nyo|Okey, Fine! Whatever!]]'' \n| Camilla\n|\n| <REF name=\"Wedding Entourage\"/><ref name=\"OK Fine, Whatever\"/>\n|-\n| 2003\u201304 \n| ''[[Basta't Kasama Kita]]'' \n| Alex\n|\n|\n|-\n| 2003-04\n| ''[[Ang Tanging Ina#Ang Tanging Ina .28TV Series.29|Ang Tanging Ina]]'' \n| Getrudis \"Tudis\" Macaspac\n|\n|\n|-\n| 2005 \n| ''[[Ok Fine 'To Ang Gusto Nyo|Okey, Fine! 'To Ang Gusto Nyo!]]'' \n| Camilla\n|\n|\n|- \n| 2006 \n| ''[[Ok Fine 'To Ang Gusto Nyo|Okey, Fine! OK Fine, Oh Yes!]]'' \n| Camilla\n|\n|\n|- \n| 2007 \n| ''[[Walang Kapalit]]'' \n| Recy\n|\n