ps://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=2479&dat=20020629&id=mq41AAAAIBAJ&sjid=dyUMAAAAIBAJ&pg=1897,6225861&hl=en | title = The Girls of \u2018OK Fine, Whatever\u2019 just Wanna have Fun | author = Valle, Jocelyn | publisher = [[Philippine Daily Inquirer]] | via = [[Google News]] | date = 29 June 2002 | accessdate = 14 October 2016}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Jologs\">{{cite web | url = https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=2479&dat=20020608&id=DVs1AAAAIBAJ&sjid=kiUMAAAAIBAJ&pg=995,40030298&hl=en | title = Nikki Valdez does Concert Tour for Religious Group | publisher = [[Philippine Daily Inquirer]] | via = [[Google News]] | date = 8 June 2002 | accessdate = 12 October 2016}}</ref> \n\n<ref name=\"Babe\">{{cite web | url = https://www.philstar.com/entertainment/2010/03/29/561964/sam-anne-team-babe-i-love-you | author = Orosa, Rosalinda L. | title = Sam, Anne Team up in Babe, I Love You | publisher = [[The Philippine Star]] | date = 29 March 2010 | accessdate =  22 September 2018}}</ref>\n\n}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|0883684}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{Philippines-actor-stub}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Valdez, Nikki}}\n[[Category:Star Magic]]\n[[Category:Star Magic Batch 4]]\n[[Category:Filipino television actresses]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Filipino comedians]]\n[[Category:Filipino film actresses]]\n[[Category:Filipino women comedians]]\n[[Category:ABS-CBN personalities]]\n[[Category:1979 births]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Filipino actress}}\n{{BLP sources|date=January 2013}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name         = Nikki Valdez\n| image        = \n| birth_name   = Ma. Alinica Valdez Garcia\n| birth_date   = {{birth date and age|1979|1|25}}\n| birth_place  = [[San Pedro, Laguna]]    [[Philippines]]\n| occupation   = [[Actress]], [[TV personality]]\n| years_active = 1993\u2013present\n| agent        = [[Star Magic]] (1993\u2013present)<br />[[ABS-CBN Entertainment]]<br />(1993\u2013present)\n| homepage     = \n| notable role = \n}}\n'''Ma. Alinica Valdez Garcia''', also known by her screen name '''Nikki Valdez''' (born January 25, 1979), is a [[Filipino people|Filipino]] actress and singer.\n\nShe is best known to play supporting roles to lead actors such as [[Jolina Magdangal]] (''Hey Babe'') in 1999 and [[Claudine Barretto]] (''Got 2 Believe'') in 2002 as ''kikay'' or sassy friend roles. In 2003, she played the role of an older sister in ''Ang Tanging Ina''. She would later star in the late Wenn Deramas' later works. In 2007, she came back to TV in the soap opera ''Walang Kapalit'' with Claudine Barretto and [[Piolo Pascual]] as the leads.\n\n==Career==\nIn the music scene she was known for a ballad called \"Meron Ba?\", for the soundtrack of ''G-Mik the Movie'' and ''Trip the Movie'' (2002), and starred in the lead role for ''F.L.A.M.E.S'' (1996-2002) TV series. She resumed her career soon after marrying a Canadian and having a baby. Valdez making her comeback to daytime television in the second installment of ''[[Precious Hearts Romances Presents|Precious Hearts Romances]]'' offering with ''Ang Lalaking Nagmahal sa Akin'' after her last role in ''[[Walang Kapalit]]'' in 2007. She worked with [[Kaye Abad]] and fellow newcomer Guji Lorenzana in Precious Hearts Romances third installment ''Somewhere in My Heart'' as Amanda in 2009.\n\nIn 2010, she is working on a daytime soap opera loosely based on the film ''[[Magkano ang Iyong Dangal?]]'' and co-starred with [[John Lloyd Cruz]] and [[Angel Locsin]] in the second book and second season of the successful TV series ''[[Imortal]]''.\n\nIn 2012, she worked along with Star Magic Alumni and Kapamilya Actress [[Shaina Magdayao]] and [[Jake Cuenca]] and along again with ''Magkano Ang Iyong Dangal?'' co-star [[Bangs Garcia]] in the top rated afternoon soap ''[[Kung Ako'y Iiwan Mo]]''.\n\n==Filmography==\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" <!-- Do not center -->\n|- <!-- Never add unnecessary background colors -->\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"